-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- pokemon_platinum.lua — game module for the Archipelago BizHawk connector.
--                        Pokémon Platinum (Nintendo DS, BizHawk melonDS core)
--
-- STATUS: location DETECTION + goal are REAL and SOURCE-DERIVED from the official
-- community AP world https://github.com/ljtpetersen/platinum_archipelago
-- (client.py + data_gen/locations.toml + data_gen/event_checks.toml, world
-- version 0.2.0, minimum_ap_version 0.6.7). The 761-entry location table below was
-- GENERATED by parsing data_gen/locations.toml with Python and replicating the
-- client's exact raw-id + check model (NOT hand-copied), so the ap_id → flag/var/
-- once mapping is byte-for-byte what PokemonPlatinumClient.game_watcher uses. Loads
-- crash-free on any cartridge; self-disables on a non-AP ROM (validates the NDS
-- header game title, exactly like client.validate_rom).
--
-- MEMORY MODEL (BizHawk melonDS NDS domains)
-- ───────────────────────────────────────────
--   The PokemonPlatinumClient is a BizHawkClient. Every save-data read in
--   client.py uses the "ARM9 System Bus" domain; the ROM identity read uses
--   "ROM". (DS main RAM is also exposed by melonDS as "Main RAM"; this module
--   follows the apworld and uses the SAME domain the apworld reads — "ARM9 System
--   Bus" — so the discovered pointer values stay consistent with the apworld.)
--
--   AP struct discovery (client.get_struct_addr):
--     u32 @ 0x023DFFFC ("ARM9 System Bus")  → ap_struct address (must satisfy
--       0x02000000 < addr < 0x023DFFFC). The 16-byte header at ap_struct must
--       equal  b' AP ' * 3 + version_u32_le  (AP_MAGIC=" AP ", version 1) — the
--       exact validate done before any save read. Re-checked every poll; if the
--       struct moves/clears, discovery restarts (stand-in for guarded_read).
--
--   Save block (VersionData v1, all offsets from client.py AP_VERSION_DATA[1]):
--     savedata_ptr = u32 @ ap_struct + 16 ("ARM9 System Bus")
--     vars_flags   @ savedata_ptr + 0xDC0, size 0x3E0
--                    vars  = bytes [0x000 .. 0x240)   (u16 LE array, var 0x4000+)
--                    flags = bytes [0x240 .. 0x3E0)   (bit array)
--     once_flags   @ savedata_ptr + 0xCF60 + 4, 2 bytes (16 once-location flags)
--   A re-read of ap_struct's header AND savedata_ptr after the bulk read discards
--   the sample on any change (the apworld's guarded_read contract).
--
-- LOCATION MODEL (client.VarsFlags.is_checked, by raw_id = (table<<16)|id)
--   table 0/1/2 (base/overworld/hidden) → FlagCheck : flags[id//8] & (1<<id%8),
--                                          guarded by id>0  (734 of these)
--   table 3 (once)                      → OnceCheck : once_flags[id//8] & bit (15)
--   12 base-table entries               → VarCheck  : op(vars_u16[id-0x4000],val)
--                                          (ops used: eq, ge)
--   table 4 (dex) / table 5 (trainers)  → only present with dexsanity/trainersanity,
--                                          which this world does NOT ship yet
--                                          (README "What is Missing"); never mapped
--                                          here, so they stay idle if ever seen.
--   Only ids in the slot's server-location set are reported.
--
-- GOAL (client.game_watcher): the only goal option is "champion" (Goal=0) →
--   event_checks["beat_cynthia"] = FlagCheck(id=2404) → flags byte 300 bit 4.
--
-- ITEMS: items_handling = 0b001 (RemoteItems off, the default) — the server sends
--   only THIS slot's own items and the PATCHED GAME grants its locally-found items
--   itself, so a SOLO seed plays fully and every check is reported in a multiworld.
--   Delivering REMOTE items (RemoteItems on → 0b011) is the client's guarded
--   ring-buffer write into the AP struct's remote_item_queue (offset 44, gated on
--   recv_state==1, recv_item_count, and the queue's own front/back/capacity — a
--   multi-write that MUST be confirmed in-emulator before shipping). It is
--   intentionally deferred (receive_item is a documented no-op) rather than risk a
--   wrong write — the same posture as pokemon_rb.lua / cvcotm.lua. The launcher
--   still replays the full item stream; this module just does not consume it yet.
--
-- MODULE CONTRACT (called by bizhawk_ap_connector.lua)
--   M.init(ctx) / M.poll() -> {ids} / M.is_goal_complete() -> bool /
--   M.receive_item(item_id, meta)
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

